# HasNextEntries тАФ Model and Proofs for `applied_index_upper_bound` / `has_next_entries_since`

> ЁЯФм *Lean Squad тАФ automated formal verification for `dsyme/raft-lean-squad`.*

This file provides a formal model of `RaftLog::applied_index_upper_bound` and
`RaftLog::has_next_entries_since` (`src/raft_log.rs:447тАУ491`) and proves their key
correctness properties.

## Background

`applied_index_upper_bound` computes the ceiling on which log entries may be applied:

```rust
fn applied_index_upper_bound(&self) -> u64 {
    std::cmp::min(
        self.committed,
        self.persisted + self.max_apply_unpersisted_log_limit,
    )
}
```

Normally equals `committed`.  When `max_apply_unpersisted_log_limit > 0`, allows applying
entries up to `persisted + limit` ahead of full persistence.

`has_next_entries_since(since_idx)`:

```rust
pub fn has_next_entries_since(&self, since_idx: u64) -> bool {
    let offset = cmp::max(since_idx + 1, self.first_index());
    let high = self.applied_index_upper_bound() + 1;
    high > offset
}
```

Returns `true` iff there is at least one index in `[offset, upper_bound]` that has not
been consumed since `since_idx`.

